text_content:
AEM Guides Native PDF output uses CSS-based styling for the Table of Contents. Each TOC entry gets a class .toc-level-N (1-based depth) and any outputclass value from the DITAMAP topicref/topichead is added as an additional CSS class.

PDF TEMPLATE STRUCTURE:
  pdf-template/
    layout.css          -- all TOC and body styling
    toc-template.html   -- TOC page layout (rarely modified)
    cover-template.html -- cover page

CSS CLASS MAPPING:
  DITAMAP nesting depth 1 -> .toc-level-1
  DITAMAP nesting depth 2 -> .toc-level-2
  DITAMAP nesting depth 3 -> .toc-level-3
  outputclass='foo'      -> additional class .foo on same element

SAMPLE layout.css:
  /* Base TOC levels */
  .toc-level-1 { font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 8px; }
  .toc-level-2 { font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 12px; }
  .toc-level-3 { font-size: 11pt; margin-left: 24px; color: #555; }
  /* Custom outputclass overrides */
  .toc-level-1.appendix { color: #666; font-style: italic; }
  .toc-level-1.deprecated { text-decoration: line-through; color: #999; }
  .toc-level-2.api-ref { font-family: monospace; }

TOPIC FILE for topichead:
  No topic file is needed for topichead entries. The navtitle attribute provides the TOC text directly. Only topicref entries with href need a corresponding .dita file.

KEY POINTS:
1. TOC styling is ONLY in layout.css, not in the .dita files.
2. The .toc-level-N class is auto-generated from nesting depth.
3. outputclass on topicref/topichead adds a class to that specific TOC entry.
4. To style ALL level-1 entries: use .toc-level-1 { ... }
5. To style SPECIFIC entries: use .toc-level-1.outputclass { ... }
6. Page numbers and leaders use ::after pseudo-element on TOC entries.
7. The PDF template must be assigned to the DITAMAP in AEM Guides output preset.

correct_examples:
DITAMAP:
<bookmap>
  <chapter>
    <topichead navtitle="Installation" outputclass="install-chapter">
      <topicref href="prerequisites.dita"/>
      <topicref href="setup.dita"/>
    </topichead>
  </chapter>
</bookmap>

layout.css:
.toc-level-1.install-chapter {
  color: #059669;
  font-weight: 700;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #d1fae5;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
}

Multi-level styling:
.toc-level-1 { font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; color: #1e293b; }
.toc-level-2 { font-size: 12pt; color: #334155; margin-left: 12px; }
.toc-level-3 { font-size: 11pt; color: #64748b; margin-left: 24px; }
.toc-level-1.appendix { font-style: italic; color: #6b7280; }
.toc-level-2.api { font-family: "Source Code Pro", monospace; }
